author: hiranya
msg: Implementing the proposal for handling responses which do not contain a Content-Type header. See SYNAPSE-587 for details. Now when the content type is not present on the response Synapse will try to provide a content type by looking at the context properties or if not assign a default value (application/octet-stream) as specified in the HTTP specs.
